### Sign Request Fields API Tests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@token = {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 1. Login as admin
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@acme.local",
  "password": "Admin123!@#"
}

### 2. Create a sign request (draft)
# @name createSignRequest
POST {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "document_id": 1,
  "title": "Test Sign Request with Fields",
  "message": "Please sign this document",
  "signers": [
    {
      "email": "signer1@example.com",
      "name": "Signer One",
      "role": "Approver"
    },
    {
      "email": "signer2@example.com",
      "name": "Signer Two",
      "role": "Reviewer"
    }
  ]
}

### 3. Get editor data
GET {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests/{{createSignRequest.response.body.data.sign_request.id}}/editor
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Save fields to sign request
POST {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests/{{createSignRequest.response.body.data.sign_request.id}}/fields
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": [
    {
      "type": "signature",
      "page": 1,
      "x": 100,
      "y": 200,
      "width": 200,
      "height": 80,
      "required": true,
      "label": "Signature of Signer 1",
      "assigned_signer_id": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "page": 1,
      "x": 100,
      "y": 300,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 40,
      "required": true,
      "label": "Full Name",
      "placeholder": "Enter your full name",
      "assigned_signer_id": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "date",
      "page": 1,
      "x": 100,
      "y": 350,
      "width": 150,
      "height": 40,
      "required": true,
      "label": "Date",
      "assigned_signer_id": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "signature",
      "page": 1,
      "x": 400,
      "y": 200,
      "width": 200,
      "height": 80,
      "required": true,
      "label": "Signature of Signer 2",
      "assigned_signer_id": 2
    }
  ]
}

### 5. Get editor data again (should show saved fields)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests/{{createSignRequest.response.body.data.sign_request.id}}/editor
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Update fields (save again with changes)
POST {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests/{{createSignRequest.response.body.data.sign_request.id}}/fields
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": [
    {
      "type": "signature",
      "page": 1,
      "x": 150,
      "y": 250,
      "width": 200,
      "height": 80,
      "required": true,
      "label": "Updated Signature Position",
      "assigned_signer_id": 1
    }
  ]
}

### 7. Send sign request (generates tokens)
# @name sendSignRequest
POST {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests/{{createSignRequest.response.body.data.sign_request.id}}/send
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Try to save fields after sending (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests/{{createSignRequest.response.body.data.sign_request.id}}/fields
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "page": 1,
      "x": 100,
      "y": 100,
      "width": 200,
      "height": 40,
      "required": true,
      "label": "This should fail"
    }
  ]
}

### === PUBLIC SIGNING FLOW ===

### 9. Get signing page data (use token from database)
# Replace TOKEN_HERE with actual signing_token from signers table
GET http://localhost:4000/public/sign/TOKEN_HERE

### 10. Get document for viewing
GET http://localhost:4000/public/sign/TOKEN_HERE/document

### 11. Send OTP
POST http://localhost:4000/public/sign/TOKEN_HERE/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "signer1@example.com"
}

### 12. Submit signature with field values
POST http://localhost:4000/public/sign/TOKEN_HERE/sign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otp": "123456",
  "field_values": [
    {
      "field_id": 1,
      "value": "John Doe Signature"
    },
    {
      "field_id": 2,
      "value": "John Doe"
    },
    {
      "field_id": 3,
      "value": "2025-11-22"
    }
  ]
}
